snippet.textDisplay:
I’m so disappointed. I’m sorry I tried so hard liking this season and it was actually going well (although really sped up) until these crossover episodes. I’m so sorry but they utterly sucked. Only cool thing about it was the nod to the past versions of the characters, which I thought it was extremely cool how they connected them. But wow how the story was lacking. And how so many moments were OVERLY cringy. Also I get the point of him dying, I do. But his character would have still been worth it and still would have the same pizazz if he was living . It’s not an impressive storyline killing him off. I don’t know why shows think that it’s so revolutionary to do this. It was unnecessary. Again I understand their reasoning but it’s such bullshit. He was a ‘real’ character who had growth (which is what we fell in love with) then all of a sudden after 7/8 seasons you’re gonna tell us hey actually his growth was only for this bs anti-Monitor storyline. Seriously ouch.

Also during interviews they said the show ended last season. I don’t even find solace in that bc that means felicity never went off to join Oliver in this new universe. If the last episode is all about mourning him I will feel so betrayed. I think this ending hurt me more than Game of Thrones. Sorry I know I sound like a hater but this wasn’t fair. I stuck with it and loved every season, constantly gave it the benefit of the doubt, was so loyal then they did this? Ok.

Last thing: Also the beauty of having so many shows in this universe was that everything had its niche. And completely immersing the arrow in this plot and to end its whole story in this plot just hurt.

snippet.textDisplay: Don’t get me wrong I like who Mia has turned into after her time with Oliver but I still wish Conner was on his to become the new green arrow. First it shows that the green arrow persona is not restricted the Queen bloodline I have always admired the people who take on the name of a hero but who don’t know their predecessor personally like Miles Morales became spider-man. Second, I see him more as a leader than Mia. Third, future green arrow (Conner) vs future deathstroke (John JR.) need I say more. Forth, the son of a former villain turns into a hero is an amazing storyline. Fifth, I just feel like the whole kid of a hero becomes a hero is too common (Nora/XS).  Lastly, I have wanted to see more of Conner Hawke/Green Arrow since that legends episode!

snippet.textDisplay:
You know what would be an interesting way to edit and watch Arrow? Put it all in chronological order. Edit out all the flashback scenes from the series up to the point of him returning home, and play them contiguously as their own “season”. Call it, “The Flashback Season”. Then watch all the post Lian Yu scenes contiguously. It would put the show in a whole new context. Especially the episodes of the first season.

Imagine rewatching the first season, without flashbacks, knowing all the crap Oliver Queen went through up to that point. It would change the experience of watching the show.
